<inglise> The administrative authority may withdraw the exemption if it is established that the average amount of liquid milk sold annually by the producer retailer concerned to the final consumer is more than twice his total annual average production established pursuant to Article 8 (2) (a) of Regulation (EEC) No 1422/78 or if it is established that the producer retailer concerned ceases to respect the conditions laid down in paragraphs 2 (b) or 3 of that Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Haldusasutus v&otilde;ib vabastuse t&uuml;histada, kui tehakse kindlaks, et asjaomase jaem&uuml;&uuml;jast tootja poolt l&otilde;pptarbijale m&uuml;&uuml;dava joogipiima keskmine aastakogus on enam kui kaks korda suurem tema keskmisest aastatoodangust, mis on kindlaks tehtud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1422/78 artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 2 punkti a kohaselt, v&otilde;i kui tehakse kindlaks, et asjaomane jaem&uuml;&uuml;jast tootja on lakanud j&auml;rgimast k&otilde;nealuse artikli l&otilde;ike 2 punktis b v&otilde;i l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud tingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom shall adopt the necessary measures for supervising compliance with Article 8 of Regulation (EEC) No 1422/78. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriik v&otilde;tab m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1422/78 artikli 8 j&auml;rgmise kontrollimiseks vajalikud meetmed. </eesti>
<inglise> Producer retailers who are exempted pursuant to paragraph 1 may be required to supply the administrative authority and the MMB with information about their production, purchases and sales of milk. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt vabastatud jaem&uuml;&uuml;jast tootjatelt v&otilde;idakse n&otilde;uda, et nad esitaksid haldusasutusele ja MMB-le teabe oma toodangu ning piima ostu ja m&uuml;&uuml;gi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Other producers who sell milk to producer retailers exempted pursuant to paragraph 1 may be required to supply to the administrative authority and the MMB information about their sales to these producer retailers. </inglise>
<eesti> Teistelt tootjatelt, kes m&uuml;&uuml;vad piima l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt vabastatud jaem&uuml;&uuml;jatest tootjatele, v&otilde;idakse n&otilde;uda, et nad esitaksid haldusasutusele ja MMB-le teabe m&uuml;&uuml;gi kohta k&otilde;nealustele jaem&uuml;&uuml;jatest tootjatele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 (2) and (3) shall apply by analogy to these measures. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 2 l&otilde;ikeid 2 ja 3 kohaldatakse analoogia p&otilde;hjal k&otilde;nealuste meetmete suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom shall adopt the necessary detailed provisions for continuing supervision of compliance with Article 9 of Regulation (EEC) No 1422/78. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriik v&otilde;tab vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1422/78 artikli 9 j&auml;rgmise pidevaks kontrollimiseks vajalikud &uuml;ksikasjalikud s&auml;tted. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> These provisions shall determine in particular for the application of paragraph 1 of that Article: </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealustes s&auml;tetes m&auml;&auml;ratakse k&otilde;nealuse artikli l&otilde;ike 1 kohaldamiseks eelk&otilde;ige kindlaks: </eesti>
<inglise> - a definition of the possible "uses" in the sense of paragraph 1 (a), </inglise>
<eesti> - l&otilde;ike 1 punktis a osutatud v&otilde;imalike kasutusotstarvete m&auml;&auml;ratlus, </eesti>
<inglise> - the "other criteria" of an objective nature which may be taken into consideration under the procedure laid down in paragraph 4 of that Article. </inglise>
<eesti> - muud objektiivsed kriteeriumid, mida v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta arvesse k&otilde;nealuse artikli l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Differentiating the selling price on the basis of the use to which the milk is put or on the basis of other objective criteria shall only be excluded in so far as it could lead to a discrimination between milk buyers and in so far as it may be an obstacle to the normal functioning of the common market organization and, in particular, its intervention system and Community aid schemes. </inglise>
<eesti> M&uuml;&uuml;gihindade eristamisest piima kasutusotstarbe v&otilde;i muude objektiivsete kriteeriumite p&otilde;hjal tuleb loobuda &uuml;ksnes sedav&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd see v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada piimaostjate seas diskrimineerimist ning takistada &uuml;hise turukorralduse ja eriti selle sekkumiss&uuml;steemi ja &uuml;henduse abikavade tavap&auml;rast toimimist. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The minimum level of the selling prices referred to in Article 9 of Regulation (EEC) No 1422/78 shall be finally determined within the month immediately following the month of delivery of the milk to the buyer and may not be subject to any subsequent reduction, rebate or discount. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1422/78 artiklis 9 osutatud m&uuml;&uuml;gihindade miinimumtase m&auml;&auml;ratakse l&otilde;plikult kindlaks piima ostjale tarnimise kuule vahetult j&auml;rgneva kuu jooksul ning selle suhtes ei tohi hiljem kohaldada mingit v&auml;hendamist, alandamist ega allahindlust. </eesti>
<inglise> This provision shall not, however, prevent bona fide adjustments being made in exceptional cases, in particular where the milk delivered does not comply with the qualitative standards applicable to the transaction concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev s&auml;te ei takista siiski erandjuhtudel heas usus kohanduste tegemist, eriti juhul, kui tarnitud piim ei vasta asjaomase tehingu suhtes kohaldatavatele kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> For the application of Article 9 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 1422/78, the United Kingdom shall adopt measures for the comparison on a regular basis of the first-hand selling prices realized on the United Kingdom market by the principal milk products made from milk sold by the MMB and by similar milk products imported into the United Kingdom from other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1422/78 artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaldamisel v&otilde;tab &Uuml;hendkuningriik meetmeid, et v&otilde;rrelda korrap&auml;raselt MMB m&uuml;&uuml;dud piimast valmistatud p&otilde;hiliste piimatoodete esmam&uuml;&uuml;gihinda &Uuml;hendkuningriigi turul teistest liikmesriikidest &Uuml;hendkuningriiki imporditud samasuguste piimatoodete esmam&uuml;&uuml;gihinnaga. </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom shall communicate each month to the Commission the lowest first-hand selling price on the United Kingdom market for a commercially significant quantity of each of the principal domestic milk products and milk products imported from other Member States sold on that market during the previous month. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriik teatab komisjonile iga kuu iga p&otilde;hilise kodumaise piimatoote kaubanduslikult olulise koguse madalaima esmam&uuml;&uuml;gihinna ning teistest liikmesriikidest imporditud ja k&otilde;nealusel turul eelmise kuu jooksul m&uuml;&uuml;dud piimatoodete madalaima esmam&uuml;&uuml;gihinna &Uuml;hendkuningriigi turul. </eesti>
<inglise> The prices communicated should be for comparable qualities. </inglise>
<eesti> Teatatud hinnad peaksid kehtima v&otilde;rreldavate kvaliteetide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> In cases where the first-hand selling price realized on the United Kingdom market by a commercially significant quantity of a domestic product falls below the lowest price of a commercially significant quantity of the milk product of a comparable quality imported from other Member States, an administrative authority, independent of the MMB appointed by the United Kingdom, shall investigate the price realized by the domestic product to determine whether it has fallen below the lowest price of the equivalent imported product as a result of the selling price applied by the MMBs for milk. </inglise>
<eesti> Juhul kui kodumaise toote kaubanduslikult olulise koguse madalaim m&uuml;&uuml;gihind &Uuml;hendkuningriigi turul on langenud alla teisest liikmesriikidest imporditud v&otilde;rreldava kvaliteediga piimatoote kaubanduslikult olulise koguse madalaima hinna, uurib MMB-st s&otilde;ltumatu &Uuml;hendkuningriigi m&auml;&auml;ratud haldusasutus kodumaise toote hinda, et otsustada, kas k&otilde;nealuse hinna langemise vastava imporditud toote madalaimast hinnast madalamale on p&otilde;hjustanud MMBs piima suhtes kohaldatav m&uuml;&uuml;gihind. </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom shall communicate the results of these investigations to the Commission within one month of the authority concerned completing its enquiry. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriik saadab k&otilde;nealuse uurimise tulemused komisjonile &uuml;he kuu jooksul p&auml;rast seda, kui asjaomane asutus on uurimise l&otilde;petanud. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Any complaints about failure to comply with Article 9 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 1422/78 shall be submitted initially to the administrative authority referred to in paragraph 5 together with full supporting evidence. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik kaebused m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1422/78 artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 3 j&auml;rgimata j&auml;tmise kohta esitatakse koos kogu t&otilde;endusmaterjaliga esmalt l&otilde;ikes 5 osutatud haldusasutusele. </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom shall communicate to the Commission a copy of every complaint and of the reasoned reply given to the complainant. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriik saadab komisjonile koopia igast kaebusest ja kaebuse esitajale antud p&otilde;hjendatud vastusest. </eesti>
<inglise> A reasoned reply shall be dispatched to the complainant within two months of receipt by the administrative authority of the complaint. </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;hjendatud vastus saadetakse kaebuse esitajale kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast seda, kui haldusasutus on kaebuse saanud. </eesti>
<inglise> 7. </inglise>
<eesti> 7. </eesti>
<inglise> If the administrative authority referred to in paragraph 5 establishes that the selling price applied by any of the MMBs for milk for any particular use is in contravention of Article 9 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 1422/78, then the United Kingdom shall immediately take the necessary measures to ensure compliance, in particular that the MMB or MMBs concerned make the appropriate adjustments in their selling prices for the milk in question and for future sales. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui l&otilde;ikes 5 osutatud haldusasutus teeb kindlaks, et mis tahes MMB poolt mis tahes kasutusotstarbeks etten&auml;htud piima suhtes kohaldatav m&uuml;&uuml;gihind on vastuolus m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1422/78 artikli 9 l&otilde;ikega 3, v&otilde;tab &Uuml;hendkuningriik viivitamata vajalikud meetmed k&otilde;nealuse l&otilde;ike j&auml;rgimise tagamiseks ja eriti selleks, et asjaomased MMBd teeksid k&otilde;nealuse piima m&uuml;&uuml;gihindades tulevast m&uuml;&uuml;ki silmas pidades asjakohased kohandused. </eesti>
<inglise> Details of these measures shall be communicated immediately to the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende meetmete &uuml;ksikasjad edastatakse viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 8. </inglise>
<eesti> 8. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 (2) and (3) shall apply by analogy to the provisions adopted by the United Kingdom pursuant to the present Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 2 l&otilde;ikeid 2 ja 3 kohaldatakse analoogia p&otilde;hjal &Uuml;hendkuningriigi poolt k&auml;esoleva artikli kohaselt vastu v&otilde;etud s&auml;tete suhtes. </eesti>
